The South-South All Progressives Congress (APC) group known as Young Stakeholders Forum (YSF) has called for total reconciliation within the party to ensure victory of the party. The group’s coordinator, Charles Ibinabo advised the party’s national leadership to reach out to some personalities and ensure total reconciliation among its members. Ibinabo specifically called on the presidency to convene an urgent roundtable meeting with all the aggrieved governorship aspirants in the state and secure their commitment to the election. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY He said Timi Alaibe’s political family, including former Bayelsa State party chairman, Chief Tiwe Orunimighe and the former APC Deputy National Publicity Secretary, Comrade Timi Frank, who had predicted victory for the APC, among others, should be engaged. The group said the chances of the APC taking over Bayelsa were currently very high. Lyon, Diri set to clash in Bayelsa gov’ship contest 10 Things Oshiomhole must do Govs, ex-govs pose threat to APC reconciliation moves in states